.SH NAME
AsyncDisposableStack.AsyncDisposableStack \- AsyncDisposableStack()
constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]AsyncDisposableStack()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates
\f[CR]AsyncDisposableStack\f[R] objects.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new AsyncDisposableStack()
.EE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]AsyncDisposableStack()\f[R] can only be
constructed with \f[CR]new\f[R].
Attempting to call it without \f[CR]new\f[R] throws a
\f[CR]TypeError\f[R].
.RE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]AsyncDisposableStack\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating an AsyncDisposableStack
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] disposer = \f[B]new\f[R] AsyncDisposableStack();
disposer.defer(() \f[B]=>\f[R] console.log(\(dqDisposed!\(dq));
\f[B]await\f[R] disposer.disposeAsync();
\f[I]// Logs: Disposed!\f[R]
.EE
